The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Tuesday, July 31, 2007

 Guru Purnima

 An evening of classical music and dance, presented by Madhyami on the occasion of Guru Purnima, at Sisir Mancha, 5pm.

 Launch

 Paschimbange Musalman Ekti Parikrama to be launched at Seagull Bookstores, 6.30pm. 

 Exhibition

 Hand embroidered and painted saris, salwar kurtas and linen by Rhitis Creations at Academy of Fine Arts, 3pm to 8pm.

 Rakhis, apparels, accessories and more in Glimpses at Moksh, 22 Camac Street, 10am to 8pm.

 Art watch

 Opening of Waterish, water colour paintings by Ekta Singha, at Academy of Fine Arts (West Gallery), 6pm.

 Birth Centenary Show of Gobardhan Ash at Aakriti Art Gallery, 3pm to 7pm. 

 Exhibition of sculptures by Bipin Goswami, Shankar Ghosh and Tapas Sarkar at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm. 

 My Butterfly Life, paintings by Tapan Karmakar, at Gallery Sanskriti, 11am to 8pm.

 Svikriti at Birla Academy of Art and Culture, 3pm to 8pm.

 The Power of Three, works by Amal Ghosh, Nabanita Javed and Kashmiri Khosa, at K2 Gallery, 11am to 7pm. 

 Sculptures, tapestries and ceramics at GC Laha Centenary Fine Arts Gallery, 1pm to 7pm.

 Paintings by Sanjib Roy at Kanvas Art Gallery, 3pm to 7pm. 

 Paintings by Maichel Bose at Gaganendra Pradarshashala, 1pm to 3pm. 

 Paintings by Tarun Ray, Ajoy Das and Sajal Kanti Mitra at Chemould, 2pm to 7pm. 




